{{!
    @template mod_booking/col_location

    Location cell for a deep (3+ levels) entity hierarchy: shows only the selected entity, linked,
    with the superordinate levels in a pure-CSS hover card (also shown on keyboard focus, see
    styles.css .mod-booking-location-cell). Screenreaders get the full path as visually hidden text
    inside the link, so the card itself is aria-hidden. Ancestor images are optional (setting
    booking/showlocationimages) and decorative (empty alt, name is rendered next to them).

    Classes required for JS:
    * none — hover/focus behaviour is pure CSS

    Context variables required for this template:
    * url - link to the entity view page
    * name - the selected entity's name
    * pathtext - full ancestor path as plain text ("Root / … / Parent")
    * ancestors - array of {name, indent, imageurl} root-first; imageurl may be null

    Example context (json):
    {
        "url": "https://example.com/local/entities/view.php?id=6",
        "name": "Raumbereich 1",
        "pathtext": "Hauptgebäude / Seminarraum 1",
        "ancestors": [
            { "name": "Hauptgebäude", "indent": 0, "imageurl": "https://example.com/pluginfile.php/1/local_entities/image/2/main.jpg" },
            { "name": "Seminarraum 1", "indent": 1, "imageurl": null }
        ]
    }
}}
<span class="mod-booking-location-cell">
    <a href="{{url}}">{{name}}<span class="sr-only visually-hidden">, {{pathtext}}</span></a>
    <span class="mod-booking-location-path" aria-hidden="true">
        {{#ancestors}}
        <span class="mod-booking-location-pathitem" style="padding-left: {{indent}}rem;">
            {{#imageurl}}<img src="{{imageurl}}" alt="" loading="lazy" class="mod-booking-location-pathimg">{{/imageurl}}{{name}}
        </span>
        {{/ancestors}}
    </span>
</span>
